President Trump delivered remarks at the First Church of Pearland in Texas, thanking Governor Abbott and others for their hard work in responding to Hurricane Harvey. He also mentioned that National Prayer Day was coming up and encouraged people to pray and enjoy the day. The President praised Senator Ted Cruz and mentioned that they signed authorizations to push through relief efforts. He acknowledged the progress in cleaning up the water and thanked the hardworking people involved. Trump introduced Ben Carson, Elaine Duke, Betsy DeVos, David Shulkin, and the First Lady of Texas, and praised their contributions. He also spoke about improvements in the Veterans Administration and the ability for veterans to choose their own doctors. The President thanked everyone for their efforts and encouraged continued progress in the recovery process.